 MBOMBELA – South African Weather Service has issued a warning for Mbombela and surrounding areas for heavy rain and possible floods.  Weather SA forecaster Victoria Nurse said the weather warning was issued to day. “There is a heavy rainfall leading to flooding warning.” She said the weather should start clearing  by tomorrow afternoon or late morning. “Things should return to normal as forecasted for the next seven days.” The department of Safety, Security and Liason’s Zandile Mandlazi said in the Ehlanzeni District, since yesterday morning, five road accidents have been reported. No fatalaties were reported but two people were seriously injured when two trucks collided on the N4 near Waterval Boven at around 15:30. “So far for the whole province, 19 accidents were reported since yesterday morning.” READ MORE HERE: 5 tips for driving in wet weather 